# Firebase Configuration
# Replace these values with your Firebase project credentials
# Get them from: Firebase Console → Project Settings → General → Your apps

# Required - Found in Firebase Console → Project Settings → General → Your apps → Web app
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# How to set up:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select existing
# 3. Add a Web app (</> icon)
# 4. Copy the firebaseConfig values and replace the placeholders above
# 5. Enable Authentication (Email/Password, Google) in Firebase Console
# 6. Enable Firestore Database in Firebase Console
# 7. Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
